{
  "texts": [
    "In the administration area, there is a common need to make decisions upon vast amounts of personal data subjects, such as student recruitment, admissions, scholarship allocation, internships, and these data subjects often also include faculty and staff, encompassing various aspects of administration (Masters, 2023).",
    "Therefore, a typical application is to use GAI as an auxiliary judgment tool to improve decision-making efficiency.",
    "However, improper use can lead to false associations between certain dimensions of personal data (e.g., race, gender, or religion) and the decision-making objective (e.g., admit or not).",
    "These biased GAI predictions may influence the final decisions made by humans.",
    "Belgodere et al. (2023) conducted the study on an admission bar exam dataset sourced from the Law School Admission Council (LSAC)."
  ]
}